    <article>
<h2 id="faq" sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="1" sourceendlinenumber="1">FAQ</h2>

<ol sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="2" sourceendlinenumber="15">
<li sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="2" sourceendlinenumber="3"><p sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="2" sourceendlinenumber="3">What is Advanced Scene Manager?<br>
Advanced Scene Manager (ASM) is a scene manager for unity, that simplifies additive scene management.</p>
</li>
<li sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="5" sourceendlinenumber="11"><p sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="5" sourceendlinenumber="11">What <em>can</em> ASM do?<br>
a) Organize scenes into collections, which allows us to mass open / close scenes.</br>
b) Open scene and collections from UnityEvent.<br>
c) Easily set scenes or collections as persistent.</br>
d) Preload scenes.<br>
e) Loading screens.</br>
f) More customizable splash screens.<br></p>
</li>
<li sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="13" sourceendlinenumber="15"><p sourcefile="faq/faq.md" sourcestartlinenumber="13" sourceendlinenumber="15">What <em>cannot</em> ASM do?<br>
a) Stream scenes - We&#39;re not a world streamer. ASM focuses on general scene management.</br>
b) Preload multiple scenes at once - this is a unity limitation, not something we can work around.<br></p>
</li>
</ol>
</article>
